Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.20,0:01:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\b1}注意 近日移除
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.20,0:01:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞西利亚是第一个\N{\rEng}Cecilia was the first to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.81,0:02:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么弄成这样?  宝贝\N{\rEng}What are you doing here?  Honey
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.71,0:02:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还小未经世事\N{\rEng}You're not old enough to know how bad life gets.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.01,0:02:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然 医生\N{\rEng}Obviously, doctor
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.08,0:02:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从未当过13岁的女孩\N{\rEng}you've never been a 13 year old girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.01,0:02:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0070,,{\fs26\b0\bord0\fsp6}处女之死
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.89,0:02:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个人都记得我们的邻居\N{\rEng}Everyone dates the demise of our neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.99,0:02:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本女孩们自杀的日子\N{\rEng}from the suicides of the Lisbon girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.53,0:02:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人们在无精打采的榆树\N{\rEng}People saw their clairvoyants in the wiped out elms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.88,0:03:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\b1}密歇根州 25年前
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.96,0:03:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和日渐衰落的汽车工业中瞥见她们犀利的眼神\N{\rEng}and the continuing decline of our auto industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.33,0:03:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,年少的我们试着把碎片拼贴完整\N{\rEng}Even then we tried putting the pieces together.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.97,0:03:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,仍是失败了\N{\rEng}We still can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.41,0:03:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在每当我们在商务餐会或鸡尾派对上相遇\N{\rEng}now whenever we meet at business lunches or cocktail parties
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.21,0:03:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都会不由得在角落里重温那些证据\N{\rEng}we find ourselves going over the evidence one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.15,0:03:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只为了解那五个女孩\N{\rEng}All to understand those five girls,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.42,0:03:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,经过这么多年 她们仍铭刻在我们的脑海\N{\rEng}who, after all these years, we can't get out of our minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.52,0:03:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞西利亚 最小的一个 13岁\N{\rEng}Cecilia, the youngest, was 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.03,0:03:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯 14岁\N{\rEng}And Lux was 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.77,0:03:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邦妮 15岁\N{\rEng}Bonnie was 15.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.54,0:03:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玛丽 16岁\N{\rEng}Mary was 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:03:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特瑞丝17岁\N{\rEng}And Therese was 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.01,0:03:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人明白我们的数学老师\N{\rEng}No one understood how Mrs. Lisbon and Mr. Lisbon,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.91,0:03:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本先生和她夫人\N{\rEng}our Math teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.02,0:03:57.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么会造出这么美丽的尤物\N{\rEng}had produced such beautiful creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.59,0:04:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗·巴蒂诺说\N{\rEng}Paul Baldino said
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞西利亚的初次自杀是他发现的\N{\rEng}he found Cecilia on her first attempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.56,0:04:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我发现她的\N{\rEng}l was the one who found her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.93,0:04:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我站在我家的下水道里\N{\rEng}l was standing in the sewers around my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.42,0:04:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能从那儿进入任何人的家\N{\rEng}Through those tunnels you can get into anyone's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.30,0:04:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们信以为真\N{\rEng}when Paul said this We believed him
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.63,0:04:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他爸是美国大兵 鲨鱼巴蒂诺\N{\rEng}because Paul's dad was Sammy the Shark Baldino
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.44,0:04:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道他的逃生隧道经过下水道\N{\rEng}and his escape tunnel led through the sewers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.61,0:04:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是想去\N{\rEng}So l was thinking to see
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.17,0:04:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看她们洗澡\N{\rEng}one of those lesbian girls taking a shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.38,0:04:26.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对 是的\N{\rEng}Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接着我进去了…到处都是血!\N{\rEng}And l walk in... And l see blood everywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.62,0:04:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我转身 顺着隧道原路返回\N{\rEng}So l turned around and went right back out the tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.39,0:04:39.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我必须告诉你们这事 回见\N{\rEng}l had to tell you guys that story. See you guys later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.60,0:04:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听说那是意外\N{\rEng}l heard it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.64,0:04:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 根本不是意外 只怪她父母\N{\rEng}lt was no accident. The parents are to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.34,0:04:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听说他们在马桶里找到刀片\N{\rEng}l heard they found the razor in the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.21,0:04:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对塞西利亚自杀的原因 众说纷纭\N{\rEng}Everyone had opinions why Cecilia tried to kill herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.51,0:04:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她不想死\N{\rEng}That girl didn't want to die
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.09,0:05:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只是想从家里逃出来\N{\rEng}she just wanted out of that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.18,0:05:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她想摆脱那种装潢方式\N{\rEng}She wanted out of that decorating scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.22,0:05:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最流行的理论认为\N{\rEng}The most popular theory
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.53,0:05:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多米尼克·帕拉佐是罪魁祸首\N{\rEng}held Dominic Palazzolo to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.19,0:05:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,多米尼克是个移民 暂时住在亲威家\N{\rEng}Dominic was an immigrant who was staying with relatives
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.90,0:05:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到他的家人在新墨西哥安家\N{\rEng}until his family got settled in New Mexico.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.23,0:05:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是街坊里第一个戴墨镜的男孩\N{\rEng}He was the first boy here to wear sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.37,0:05:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来了还不到一周他就恋爱了\N{\rEng}Within a week of arriving he'd fallen in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.04,0:05:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他心仪的对象不是塞西利亚\N{\rEng}The object of his desire wasn't Cecilia,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是黛安娜·波特\N{\rEng}but Diana Porter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我爱她!\N{\rEng}l love her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.98,0:05:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,黛安娜去瑞士度假时 多米尼克逆天而行\N{\rEng}When Diana Porter left on vacation, Dominic denounced God.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.86,0:05:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为表真心\N{\rEng}And to prove to Olivia his love
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.75,0:05:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他从亲戚家的房顶跳下去了\N{\rEng}he jumped off the roof of his relatives' house.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.99,0:06:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要给你看一些图象\N{\rEng}l'm going to show you some images.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.22,0:06:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后… 呃 你告诉我\N{\rEng}And... er, you tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.33,0:06:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想到了什么\N{\rEng}what they remind you of.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.63,0:06:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吗?\N{\rEng}OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.18,0:06:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香蕉\N{\rEng}A banana.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.66,0:06:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沼泽\N{\rEng}A swamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.60,0:06:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸头\N{\rEng}An Afro.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.95,0:07:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我认为塞西利亚并不真想自杀\N{\rEng}l don't think that Cecilia truly meant to end her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.73,0:07:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她的举动是求助的呐喊\N{\rEng}Her act was a cry for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.63,0:07:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你们非常严格\N{\rEng}l know you're very strict,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.23,0:07:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但建立一些校外社交关系\N{\rEng}but l think that Cecilia would benefit by having
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.07,0:07:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对塞西利亚十分有益\N{\rEng}a social outlet outside of the codification of school.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.61,0:07:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟同龄的男孩交往交往\N{\rEng}And interact with males her own age.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.65,0:07:51.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彼得帮里斯本先生\N{\rEng}Peter helped Mr. Lisbon install a model
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.26,0:07:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在教室建了个太阳系模型\N{\rEng}of the solar system in his classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.59,0:07:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,作为回报 里斯本先生请他来吃晚饭\N{\rEng}ln return, Mr. Lisbon invited him for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.89,0:07:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保佑我们 主啊为了这些\N{\rEng}Bless us, O Lord, in these, Thy gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.36,0:08:03.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们因耶稣之慷慨而收到的礼物 阿门\N{\rEng}which we receive from Thy bounty through Christ. Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.40,0:08:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,阿门\N{\rEng}Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.30,0:08:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯 把上衣穿上 抱歉\N{\rEng}Lux, please put your shirt on this instant. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 宝贝儿 把盐递过来好吗?\N{\rEng}Thank you, dear. Can you pass the salt, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.88,0:08:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要火腿吗? 谢谢\N{\rEng}Ham? Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.62,0:08:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甜心 要点儿豌豆吗? 我讨厌豌豆\N{\rEng}Sweetheart, would you like some peas? l hate peas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.09,0:08:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,火腿看上去真不错 亲爱的\N{\rEng}lt's a nice looking ham, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.79,0:08:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 亲爱的 真不错 妈妈\N{\rEng}Well, thank you, honey. This is good, mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么 彼得 你是个飞机狂热者吗?\N{\rEng}So, Peter, are you an aviation enthusiast?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.23,0:08:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 我不知道是否该把自己称作狂热者\N{\rEng}Well, l don't know if l'd call myself an enthusiast.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我喜欢飞机\N{\rEng}l like planes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.74,0:08:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彼得 你是橄榄球队的吗?\N{\rEng}Peter, are you on the football squad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.51,0:08:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 我玩儿这个 但不在队里\N{\rEng}No. l play, but l'm not on the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.11,0:08:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 我知道了 不是队员\N{\rEng}Oh, l see. Not a team player.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.65,0:08:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你喜欢摔跤吗?\N{\rEng}Do you like to wrestle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.55,0:09:00.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还好吧?\N{\rEng}Are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.79,0:09:04.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一种巴西青蛙今天被列入濒危物种了\N{\rEng}A Brazilian frog entered the endangered species list today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今年的第三种了\N{\rEng}That's the third animal this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.60,0:09:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 宝贝儿 我头一次听说\N{\rEng}Oh, dear. Darling, l've never heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.20,0:09:14.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不好意思 我可以用一下厕所吗? 当然\N{\rEng}Excuse me. May l use the restroom? Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.00,0:09:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,楼下的坏了\N{\rEng}The one down here isn't working very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.13,0:09:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去楼上塞西利亚的房间\N{\rEng}Go upstairs through Cecilia's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.18,0:09:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 谢谢\N{\rEng}OK, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.18,0:10:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\b1}卫生棉条
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.95,0:10:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等等\N{\rEng}Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.18,0:10:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为你死在里边了\N{\rEng}l thought you'd died in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.95,0:10:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你霸占完厕所了吗? 我需要点东西\N{\rEng}Are you done hogging the bathroom? l need something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,介意回避一下吗?\N{\rEng}Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.04,0:10:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,非常谢谢 你忘了东西\N{\rEng}Thank you. Are you forgetting something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.95,0:11:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彼得 这是一片空气箔… 谢谢\N{\rEng}Peter, here's an air foil... Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.58,0:11:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是柏得利原理的应用\N{\rEng}lt's a demonstration of Bernoulli's Principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.62,0:11:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,举起…\N{\rEng}Lift...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.02,0:11:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从那以后 里斯本家的就开始变样了\N{\rEng}From then on the Lisbon house began to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.66,0:11:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几乎每天\N{\rEng}Almost every day
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.07,0:11:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甚至不用照看塞西利亚时\N{\rEng}and even when she wasn't keeping an eye on Cecilia
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.97,0:11:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯都会穿着游泳衣 坐在毛巾上晒黑\N{\rEng}Lux would suntan on her towel, wearing a swimsuit
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.79,0:11:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换来15分钟\N{\rEng}that caused the knife sharpener
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.10,0:11:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,免费磨刀演示\N{\rEng}to give her a 15 minute demonstration for free.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.45,0:11:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,遵循医嘱\N{\rEng}Following the doctor's orders
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.75,0:11:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞西利亚回家两周后\N{\rEng}two weeks after Cecilia returned home
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.45,0:11:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本先生说服妻子允许女孩们举办了\N{\rEng}Mr. Lisbon persuaded his wife to let the girls throw
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.45,0:11:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,短暂人生中第一场也是唯一一场派对\N{\rEng}the first and the only party of their short lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.13,0:12:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了 这样行吗?\N{\rEng}There. ls that OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.34,0:12:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得去换衣服了\N{\rEng}l've got to get dressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.12,0:12:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎 晚上好 里斯本太太\N{\rEng}Welcome. Good evening, Mrs. Lisbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.92,0:12:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进来吧\N{\rEng}Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.76,0:12:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,派对在地下室\N{\rEng}The party's in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.86,0:12:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,左转 下楼梯\N{\rEng}Just go to the left and then down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.98,0:12:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 我是邦妮\N{\rEng}Hi, l'm Bonnie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨… 我是蒂姆 很高兴见到你\N{\rEng}Hi... Tim. Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.42,0:12:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想要点潘趣酒吗? 好的\N{\rEng}Would you like some punch? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.63,0:12:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.23,0:13:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 谢谢\N{\rEng}Hi. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.37,0:13:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 谢谢\N{\rEng}Hi. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.10,0:13:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿 嗨\N{\rEng}Hey. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.11,0:13:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想坐下吗? 好的\N{\rEng}Do you want to sit down? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.72,0:13:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你的智力测验分数怎么样?  还不错\N{\rEng}How did your SATs go?  OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.99,0:14:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好\N{\rEng}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.93,0:14:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道要申请哪所大学吗?\N{\rEng}Do you know where you're applying yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.96,0:14:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有 但我父母倾向于耶鲁\N{\rEng}No, but my parents are pushing towards Yale.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.57,0:14:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为那是我爸的母校 真不错\N{\rEng}Because that's where my dad went. That's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.71,0:14:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要想象云层散开\N{\rEng}You have to imagine the clouds opening up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.61,0:14:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨驾驶着梅塞施米特(德国战斗机)冲出阳光\N{\rEng}and out of the sun would come the Hun in his Messerschmitt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.55,0:14:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孩子们 大你们两三岁的\N{\rEng}And boys, just older than you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.86,0:14:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都开P51-B野马式战斗机\N{\rEng}would be in this, the P51 B Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.52,0:14:31.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"B"代表舷窗\N{\rEng}''B'' for bull's eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.99,0:14:37.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听说过耶鲁吗? 是的\N{\rEng}You've heard of Yale? Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.93,0:14:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,潘趣酒真不错 再来点?\N{\rEng}This punch is fantastic. More?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.23,0:14:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里边有什么?\N{\rEng}What's in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.00,0:14:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,果汁 一些樱桃… 菠萝\N{\rEng}Juices, some cherry... pineapple.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.87,0:14:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 我… 我喜欢菠萝\N{\rEng}You know, l... l love pineapple.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.81,0:14:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真的吗?\N{\rEng}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.12,0:15:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这宝贝出场了\N{\rEng}This baby would come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.49,0:15:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是它让英国打了胜仗\N{\rEng}This won the war for the United Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.68,0:15:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 没事\N{\rEng}Excuse me. Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.33,0:15:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是这个仪器让模型运转\N{\rEng}And it's this kind of equipment that makes a model work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.94,0:15:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是周\N{\rEng}Here's Joe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.54,0:15:27.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 周 嗨\N{\rEng}Hi, Joe. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.01,0:15:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果他有需要 打电话叫我\N{\rEng}lf he needs anything, call me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.36,0:15:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会没事的 I'm sure he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.45,0:15:38.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 嗨\N{\rEng}Hi. Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.96,0:15:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,周 很高兴见到你 你好吗?\N{\rEng}Joe. Good to see you. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴你今晚能来 你怎么样?\N{\rEng}Glad you came tonight. How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.40,0:15:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来的正好\N{\rEng}You're just in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.43,0:15:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨\N{\rEng}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.53,0:15:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看 如果你挠他下巴他耳朵就动\N{\rEng}Look. His ears go if you scratch his chin.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.60,0:15:57.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,周 唱你的歌\N{\rEng}Joe, sing your song.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.81,0:16:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三宝颜的猴子没尾巴\N{\fs16\fnMicrosoft\shad1\1c&H008080&}菲律宾城市\N{\rEng}Oh, the monkeys have no tails in Zamboanga
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.51,0:16:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,猴子没尾巴\N{\rEng}Oh, the monkeys have no tails
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.15,0:16:05.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,被鲸鱼吃掉啦\N{\rEng}They were bitten off by whales
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.68,0:16:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三宝颜的猴子没尾巴\N{\rEng}Oh, the monkeys have no tails in Zamboanga
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.29,0:16:15.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是首好歌 唱的好 周\N{\rEng}Good song. Good job, Joe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.49,0:16:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你从哪儿学的这首歌?\N{\rEng}Where'd you learn that song?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.16,0:16:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能离开一会儿吧?\N{\rEng}Can l be excused?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.90,0:16:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要你想 但宝贝儿 这是你的派对\N{\rEng}lf you want to, my dear, but this is your party.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.51,0:16:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧 如果你想上楼就去吧 我们…\N{\rEng}All right. lf you want to go upstairs, do. We'll just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.81,0:16:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只能在没有你的情况下玩了\N{\rEng}We'll just have to have fun without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.38,0:16:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看 他总是选正面\N{\rEng}Look. He always chooses heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.85,0:16:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,周 会是哪面? 正面\N{\rEng}Joe, what's it going to be? Heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.25,0:16:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,周 试试背面\N{\rEng}Joe, try tails.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.72,0:16:47.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是正面!\N{\rEng}Heads it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再来 正面\N{\rEng}Let's go. Heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.19,0:16:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正面! 再来一次\N{\rEng}Heads! One more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.30,0:16:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在空中 周 正面\N{\rEng}ln the air, Joe. Heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.90,0:17:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,又是正面!\N{\rEng}Heads it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再来一次 提前猜 周 正面\N{\rEng}One more time. Call in the air, Joe. Heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.88,0:17:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正面 真不错\N{\rEng}Heads. Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.00,0:17:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么样?  很好\N{\rEng}How are you doing?  Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.11,0:17:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他学的真快\N{\rEng}He picked it up really well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.46,0:17:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我最喜欢的歌\N{\rEng}This is my favorite song.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.19,0:17:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 你… 非常漂亮 像圣人一样\N{\rEng}You know, you're... very beautiful. Like a saint.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.93,0:17:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时间我可以给你画像\N{\rEng}l could paint you some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.70,0:17:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.04,0:17:35.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们唱歌了吗?\N{\rEng}Did they sing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.01,0:17:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哇 真好!\N{\rEng}Wow, that's good!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.94,0:17:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天啊!\N{\rEng}God!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.61,0:17:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 主啊!\N{\rEng}Oh, Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.51,0:17:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞西利亚!\N{\rEng}Cecilia!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.07,0:18:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 我的… 不 不 不!\N{\rEng}Oh, my...! No! No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.87,0:18:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要看 转过去\N{\rEng}Don't look. Turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.01,0:18:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,转过去! 亲爱的 转… 我的上帝!\N{\rEng}Turn around! Darlings, turn... Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.91,0:18:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 耶稣!\N{\rEng}Oh, Jesus!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.71,0:18:20.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,求你了 上帝\N{\rEng}Please, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.07,0:19:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们到了\N{\rEng}We're here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天拒办葬礼\N{\rEng}No funerals today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.71,0:19:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他说她才13岁\N{\rEng}He said she was only 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.83,0:20:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 玛丽 你父母在家吗?\N{\rEng}Hi, Mary. Are your parents home?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.40,0:20:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 神父 请进\N{\rEng}Hi, Father. Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.07,0:20:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 神父\N{\rEng}Oh. Hello, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.68,0:20:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请坐\N{\rEng}Please, sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.48,0:20:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.65,0:20:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托 那是界内球!\N{\rEng}Come on, that was inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.75,0:20:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,呃 不了 谢谢\N{\rEng}Uh, no. No, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.63,0:20:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把夫人叫下来 聊一聊好吗?\N{\rEng}How about we get the missus down here? Have a little chat?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.87,0:20:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,恐怕她不舒服 I'm afraid she's under the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.34,0:20:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她…\N{\rEng}She's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.84,0:20:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁也不见\N{\rEng}seeing anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.04,0:21:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 她会见牧师的\N{\rEng}Well, she'll see her priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.71,0:21:07.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这孩子每次都打不好界内球\N{\rEng}This kid's a sucker for the inside ones every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.38,0:21:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每次都是\N{\rEng}Every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.99,0:21:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉\N{\rEng}Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.82,0:21:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,神父…\N{\rEng}Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.27,0:21:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,双杀 神父\N{\rEng}Double play, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.37,0:21:30.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,双杀\N{\rEng}Double play.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.56,0:21:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本太太?\N{\rEng}Mrs. Lisbon?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.04,0:22:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能进来吗? 好的\N{\rEng}May l come in? OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.38,0:22:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们好 女孩们 我想我们可以谈谈\N{\rEng}Hello, girls. l thought we could talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.05,0:22:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们想聊聊吗?\N{\rEng}Do you feel like talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.62,0:22:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯… 如果你们想的话\N{\rEng}Well... if you ever want to,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.12,0:22:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们知道到哪儿找我\N{\rEng}you know where to find me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.64,0:22:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本太太? 我是穆迪神父\N{\rEng}Mrs. Lisbon? lt's Father Moody.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.84,0:22:44.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本太太 你好\N{\rEng}Mrs. Lisbon. Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.95,0:22:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想告诉你\N{\rEng}l wanted you to know that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.29,0:22:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,塞西利亚的死是个意外\N{\rEng}l listed Cecilia's death as an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.84,0:23:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一场必然发生的意外\N{\rEng}An accident waiting to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.54,0:23:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们无法自欺欺人\N{\rEng}They couldn't get a policy to cover it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.11,0:23:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是太危险了\N{\rEng}I know.lt's incredibly dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.11,0:23:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们试试\N{\rEng}Let's give it a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.31,0:23:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,准备好了? 123\N{\rEng}Ready? One, two, three.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.76,0:23:31.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太悲伤了 真让我不敢相信\N{\rEng}lt's so sad, l can't believe it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.83,0:23:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你车里的锁链呢?\N{\rEng}Have you got that chain in your truck?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.48,0:23:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开车!\N{\rEng}Hit it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.13,0:24:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们收集的里斯本女孩的纪念品保存至今\N{\rEng}Our collection of souvenirs of the Lisbon girls
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.20,0:24:18.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从塞西利亚的日记开始\N{\rEng}which still exists started with Cecilia's diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.57,0:24:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕克从水管工那儿弄来的\N{\rEng}Parkie had gotten it from the plumber's assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.47,0:24:24.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在浴室的马桶边找到它\N{\rEng}who'd found it in the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.15,0:24:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蒂姆·微纳是智者 解密了它\N{\rEng}Tim Weiner, the Brain, decoded it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.05,0:24:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感情不稳定\N{\rEng}Emotional instability.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.52,0:24:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看"i"上的圆点 每个都如是\N{\rEng}Look at the ''ls'', the dots on them. They're everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.39,0:24:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,基本上 她是个梦想家\N{\rEng}Basically, what we have here is a dreamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.33,0:24:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个完全与现实脱节的人\N{\rEng}Someone completely out of touch with reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.03,0:24:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她跳起来时 可能感觉自己要飞起来了\N{\rEng}When she jumped, she probably thought she would fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.04,0:24:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2月13日 周一 今天我们吃的冰批萨\N{\rEng}Monday, February 13th. Today we had frozen pizza.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.48,0:24:56.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,周四 妈妈晚饭做了奶油玉米\N{\rEng}Thursday. Mum made cream corn for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.77,0:25:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,糟透了 看上去就像…\N{\rEng}lt's the worst. lt looks like...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.88,0:25:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玛丽像白痴一样撞烂了门牙\N{\rEng}Mary chipped a tooth acting like an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.95,0:25:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她大吵大闹 还不得不去补牙\N{\rEng}She made a scene and had to get her tooth capped.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.19,0:25:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我猜看上去没两样 给我\N{\rEng}lt looks normal. Give me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.16,0:25:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就说她补过牙\N{\rEng}l said she had a capped tooth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.50,0:25:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,榆树! 一棵要死的树能写多少页?\N{\rEng}Elm trees! How many pages can you write about dying trees?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.34,0:25:26.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是有关多米尼克的\N{\rEng}Here's something about Dominic.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.58,0:25:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帕佐罗今天为了那阔绰婊子波特\N{\rEng}Palazzolo jumped off the roof today
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.59,0:25:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从屋顶上跳下来了\N{\rEng}over that rich bitch, Porter.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.51,0:25:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还能再蠢点么?\N{\rEng}How stupid can you be?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.45,0:25:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天我们乘船出海\N{\rEng}Today we went out on the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.72,0:25:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很冷 我们看到了几只鲸鱼\N{\rEng}lt was cold. We saw a couple of whales.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.60,0:25:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯摸了鲸鱼 没想到它们这么臭\N{\rEng}Lux stroked the whale. l didn't think they'd stink so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.83,0:25:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是它们肚子里的海草烂了\N{\rEng}lt's the kelp in their bellies rotting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.60,0:25:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望以后可以再去\N{\rEng}l hope we can go again some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.03,0:25:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,读读这个吧\N{\rEng}Let's read that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.37,0:25:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯看上了凯文…\N{\rEng}Lux lusted over Kevin...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.01,0:25:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是"海兹"吗? 那个送垃圾的男人\N{\rEng}ls it ''Heinz''? The garbage man.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.67,0:25:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯看上了凯文·海纳兹\N{\rEng}Lux lusted over Kevin Haines,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.48,0:26:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个送垃圾的男人\N{\rEng}the garbage man.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.07,0:26:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她早上5点起床 在前门台阶上转悠\N{\rEng}She'd wake up at 5am and hang out on the front steps.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.18,0:26:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就跟别人看不出来似的!\N{\rEng}Like it wasn't completely obvious!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.51,0:26:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她把他的名字写在所有的内衣上\N{\rEng}She wrote his name on all her underwear.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.32,0:26:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈妈发现了 把所有凯文的字样都漂白了\N{\rEng}Mum found them and bleached out all the Kevins.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.22,0:26:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯在床上哭了一整天\N{\rEng}Lux is crying on her bed all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.90,0:26:25.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"这些树 像充满空气的肺叶"\N{\rEng}''The trees, like lungs filling with air
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.13,0:26:29.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"我姐姐 恶毒的那个 拉我的头发"\N{\rEng}''My sister, the mean one, pulling my hair''
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.01,0:26:38.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,于是我们得以知晓她们的生活\N{\rEng}And so we started to learn about their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.41,0:26:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些记忆汇集了我们未曾经历过的时光\N{\rEng}Coming to hold the memories of times we hadn't experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.22,0:26:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们感受到作为女孩的被禁锢感\N{\rEng}We felt the imprisonment of being a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.42,0:26:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它是如何让你变得浮想联翩\N{\rEng}How it made your mind active and dreamy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.32,0:26:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让你了解到哪些颜色更搭\N{\rEng}and how you knowing when colors went together
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.19,0:26:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道女孩们都有着缜密的内心\N{\rEng}We knew that the girls were really women in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.86,0:26:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们懂得爱情 甚至死亡\N{\rEng}They understood love and even death.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.50,0:27:01.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们能做的就是吸引她们\N{\rEng}Our job was to create the noise that fascinated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.47,0:27:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们对我们了如指掌\N{\rEng}They knew everything about us
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.81,0:27:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们对她们却一无所知\N{\rEng}but we couldn't fathom them at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.92,0:27:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 里斯本太太 我是莉迪亚·皮尔 我在做… Hi. Mrs. Lisbon, I'm Lydia Perl. I'm putting together...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.80,0:27:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 我是邦妮 这是玛丽 Oh! Hi, I'm Bonnie. This is Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.23,0:27:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你好 女孩们 我来问你们几个问题… Hello, girls. I'm here to ask you a couple of questions...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.70,0:27:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是关于塞西利亚的\N{\rEng}about Cecilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.14,0:27:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯? 好的 呃…\N{\rEng}Yeah? Great. Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.61,0:27:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,或许你们能告诉我一点她的事?\N{\rEng}Maybe you could tell me a little bit about her?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.22,0:27:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她有没有什么特殊的兴趣爱好?\N{\rEng}Did she have any special interests or hobbies?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.45,0:27:55.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她很喜欢写日记\N{\rEng}She liked writing her journal a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.89,0:27:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真棒\N{\rEng}That is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.73,0:28:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 她有没…\N{\rEng}OK. Did she...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.00,0:28:03.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她有说过要结束自己的生命吗?\N{\rEng}Did she ever talk about ending her life?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.67,0:28:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,出什么事了?\N{\rEng}What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.37,0:28:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你一定是里斯本太太\N{\rEng}You must be Mrs. Lisbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.87,0:28:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是莉迪亚·皮尔 我为二频道做一档节目 I'm Lydia Perl. I'm doing a piece for Channel Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.71,0:28:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这儿不欢迎你 皮尔小姐\N{\rEng}You have to leave now, Miss Perl.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.14,0:28:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去年夏天 东部一位自杀少女\N{\rEng}The suicide of a teenager last summer
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.45,0:28:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,引发了国民危机意识\N{\rEng}has increased the awareness of a crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.35,0:28:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我站在塞西利亚·里斯本家门前 一个13岁… I'm at the home where Cecilia Lisbon...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.52,0:28:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们为什么不让她安息呢?\N{\rEng}Why don't they let her rest in peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.82,0:28:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...爱好写诗 悲剧性的结束了自己的生命\N{\rEng}..tragically put an end to her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.63,0:28:32.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,心理学家一致认为 当代青少年\N{\rEng}Psychologists agree that adolescence today
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.16,0:28:35.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比起以前\N{\rEng}is more fraught by pressures and complexities
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.86,0:28:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,更加复杂与脆弱\N{\rEng}than in years past.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.63,0:28:42.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,越来越多的医生说挫败感能引起暴力行为\N{\rEng}Doctors say that frustration can lead to acts of violence
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.46,0:28:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,青少年无法将现实\N{\rEng}whose reality the adolescent cannot separate
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.09,0:28:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与虚幻区分开来\N{\rEng}from its intended drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.81,0:28:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我烤了一个有老鼠药的馅饼\N{\rEng}l baked a pie full of rat poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.95,0:28:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得我可以悄悄吃下它\N{\rEng}l thought l could eat it without it being suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.32,0:29:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我奶奶 她都86了…\N{\rEng}My nana, who was 86...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.66,0:29:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她真的很喜欢甜食\N{\rEng}She really likes sweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.90,0:29:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她吃了三块\N{\rEng}She had three pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.17,0:29:19.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我为这个母亲感到难过 I'm sorriest for the mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.31,0:29:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 你一直想知道如何补救\N{\rEng}You'd always wonder what you could have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.88,0:29:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要挂了 再见\N{\rEng}l got to go. See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.14,0:29:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 再见\N{\rEng}All right. Bye bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.55,0:29:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\rEng}Bye bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.68,0:30:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别担心\N{\rEng}Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.05,0:30:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们把栅栏拆了\N{\rEng}They took the fence out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.80,0:30:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老天 你打鼾可够响的\N{\rEng}God, you snore loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.38,0:31:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那些女孩有光明的前途\N{\rEng}Those girls have a bright future ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.09,0:31:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,另一个却已成定局\N{\rEng}The other one was just going to end up a cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.69,0:31:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,直到9月7号\N{\rEng}We didn't see the girls together as a group
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.37,0:31:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们才见到女孩们一块出现\N{\rEng}until September 7th.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.63,0:31:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玛丽 勒克斯 邦妮和特瑞丝\N{\rEng}Mary, Lux, Bonnie and Therese,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.33,0:32:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来到学校 就像什么也没发生过\N{\rEng}came to school as though nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.37,0:32:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们觉得只要仔细看\N{\rEng}We felt if we looked hard
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.37,0:32:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就会明白她们的感觉以及她们到底是谁\N{\rEng}we'd understand their feelings and who they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.44,0:32:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 正如你记得的 这是维恩图\N{\rEng}All right. These are Venn diagrams, as you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.98,0:32:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有'A'和'B'相交\N{\rEng}lf we have ''A'' and ''B'' intersecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.59,0:32:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是'A'跟'B'\N{\rEng}And ''A'' and ''B''.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.02,0:32:21.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果'A'与'B'相交 就得出这块区域\N{\rEng}lf ''A'' intersects ''B'', we have this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.72,0:32:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果'A'与'B'相并\N{\rEng}And if ''A'' is the union with ''B''
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.01,0:32:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就得出整个圆和相交部分\N{\rEng}we have all of the circle plus the intersection.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.86,0:32:32.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是交集和并集的规则\N{\rEng}These are the laws of intersection and union. OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.64,0:32:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过的怎么样?\N{\rEng}How's it going?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.15,0:32:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还不错\N{\rEng}Not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.62,0:32:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 "素描《淑女本色》...\N{\rEng}OK. ''Do a character sketch on the following characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.60,0:32:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,中的一个角色…"\N{\rEng}from Portrait Of A Lady...''
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.09,0:33:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一个是… 罗夫\N{\rEng}The first one is... Ralph.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.23,0:33:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,呃… 他很好\N{\rEng}Um... He was nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.70,0:33:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他死时我真的很难过\N{\rEng}lt was really sad when he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.37,0:33:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 上帝 真不敢相信我刚才说了什么\N{\rEng}Oh, my gosh. l can't believe l just said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.37,0:33:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很抱歉\N{\rEng}l am so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.59,0:33:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,读到了惊人的自杀率\N{\rEng}Reading about the alarming suicide rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.72,0:33:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我与伍德哈斯先生和其他几位老师谈过了\N{\rEng}l talked to Mr. Woodhouse and some of the teachers here
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.91,0:33:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,意识到如此重大的问题\N{\rEng}and realized that nothing about this serious matter
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.08,0:33:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还未在学校里讨论过\N{\rEng}has been discussed at this school.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.87,0:33:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随后就有绿色的小册子发下来\N{\rEng}And quickly thereafter green pamphlets were distributed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.20,0:33:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们觉得绿色很欢快 也不算太欢快\N{\rEng}We felt green was cheerful, but not too cheerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.14,0:33:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,显然比红色要好\N{\rEng}Certainly better than red.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.41,0:33:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,册子里说\N{\rEng}The pamphlets has told us
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.59,0:33:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国一天有80起自杀\N{\rEng}there were 80 suicides a day in America
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.84,0:33:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一年30,000起\N{\rEng}30,000 a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.38,0:33:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,茄子!\N{\rEng}Cheese!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.88,0:33:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这敲响了我们\N{\rEng}lt alerted us to danger signals
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.07,0:33:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一直在找寻的危险警报\N{\rEng}we couldn't help but look for.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.59,0:34:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本的女孩子们瞳孔扩大了吗?\N{\rEng}Were the Lisbon girls' pupils dilated?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.42,0:34:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们对校园活动\N{\rEng}Had they lost interest in school activities
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.83,0:34:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,体育运动或爱好失去兴趣了吗?\N{\rEng}and sports and hobbies?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.03,0:34:08.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们被同龄人孤立了吗?\N{\rEng}Had they withdrawn from their peers?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.16,0:34:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 我是瑞斯 Hi, I'm Chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.60,0:34:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道你是谁\N{\rEng}l know who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.61,0:34:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我这辈子就上过这一所学校\N{\rEng}l've only been going to this school my whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.84,0:34:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用没话找话说\N{\rEng}You don't have to talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.72,0:34:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如说 我们有两种不同的经济类型\N{\rEng}So, for example we have two different types of economics
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.02,0:34:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第一种叫做宏观经济\N{\rEng}the first one is called macroeconomics.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.36,0:34:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看\N{\rEng}Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.97,0:34:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她在笑\N{\rEng}She's laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.57,0:34:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他让她笑了\N{\rEng}He made her laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.96,0:34:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这条狗嘴里哪吐得出象牙!\N{\rEng}You never heard him say anything remotely intelligent!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.83,0:34:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,与勒克斯交谈的男孩\N{\rEng}The boys who talked with Lux
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.33,0:35:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总是很蠢 也套不出任何信息\N{\rEng}were always stupid and terrible sources of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.78,0:35:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,..手风琴 她挺好\N{\rEng}...squeezebox. She's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.42,0:35:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉你吧 她绝对是学校里最辣的女孩\N{\rEng}Let me tell you, she's the hottest girl in school.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.82,0:35:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想知道发生什么了?闻我的手指吧 伙计\N{\rEng}You want to know what happened? Smell my fingers, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.83,0:35:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 她不谈起塞西利亚\N{\rEng}No, she didn't talk about Cecilia.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.79,0:35:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们并没在说话 如果你知道我的意思\N{\rEng}We weren't exactly talking, if you know what l mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.96,0:35:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,认识勒克斯的唯一可靠的男孩\N{\rEng}The only reliable boy who actually got to know Lux
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.06,0:35:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是崔普·方汀\N{\rEng}was Trip Fontaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.91,0:35:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他最近减掉了婴儿肥\N{\rEng}Who had recently lost his baby fat
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.27,0:35:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这很让女孩和妈妈们高兴\N{\rEng}to the delight of girls and mothers alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.15,0:35:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我又迟到了\N{\rEng}l'm late again.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.22,0:35:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 拜托!\N{\rEng}Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.43,0:35:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.37,0:37:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们学校的所有女孩都爱上了崔普\N{\rEng}All the girls at our school are in love with Trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.97,0:37:07.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所有的女孩 除了勒克斯\N{\rEng}All the girls, except Lux.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.98,0:37:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,崔普说 他是从上错第五节历史课\N{\rEng}Trip said his passion for Lux was started
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.64,0:37:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,开始迷上勒克斯的\N{\rEng}when he went into the wrong History class.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.75,0:37:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,按照惯例 他在外边抽大麻\N{\rEng}As was his custom, he went out to smoke the marijuana
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.79,0:37:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他像糖尿病童打胰岛素一样按时吸食大麻\N{\rEng}he took as regularly as a diabetic kid takes lnsulin.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.83,0:37:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那一天 他为了躲伍德哈斯先生\N{\rEng}On this particular day, he avoided Mr. Woodhouse
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.18,0:37:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,溜进一间教室\N{\rEng}by ducking into a class.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.38,0:37:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她是这个旋转世界中的静点\N{\rEng}She was the still point of the turning world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.55,0:37:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从未忘记过她 从来没有\N{\rEng}l never got over that girl. Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.66,0:38:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我爱过很多女人 但跟那不一样…\N{\rEng}l've loved a lot of ladies, but not like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.19,0:38:02.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是真的\N{\rEng}That was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.53,0:38:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我永远忘不了第一次见她\N{\rEng}l'll never forget the first time l saw her.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.47,0:38:11.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道是什么打动了我 我不知道该怎么办\N{\rEng}l didn't know what had hit me. l didn't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.54,0:38:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为与别的女孩总是得心应手\N{\rEng}Because it was so easy with all the other girls
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.88,0:38:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但她看都不看我\N{\rEng}but she wouldn't look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.81,0:38:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我…我不是主动追人的类型\N{\rEng}l... l was never the kind to pursue.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.47,0:38:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你知道我的意思\N{\rEng}lf you know what l mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.82,0:38:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她让我疯狂 伙计\N{\rEng}That girl drove me crazy, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.20,0:38:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真好吃\N{\rEng}Mmm, yummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.04,0:38:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯?\N{\rEng}Lux?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.11,0:38:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嘿\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.78,0:38:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看 只是面包片加肉而已\N{\rEng}Look at it. lt's just meat on bread rolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.99,0:39:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 妈妈\N{\rEng}Thanks, Mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.73,0:39:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,崔普的爸爸帮不上什么忙\N{\rEng}Trip's dad was little help.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.67,0:39:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 首先 别给她打电话\N{\rEng}Well, first off, don't call her on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.57,0:39:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这… 很奥妙\N{\rEng}lt's all... lt's all subtlety.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.58,0:39:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有细微的差别\N{\rEng}lt's all nuance.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.81,0:39:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 你只要在学校跟她说说话\N{\rEng}Yeah. You just need to talk to her at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.16,0:39:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么都行\N{\rEng}About anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.23,0:39:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天气… 或作业\N{\rEng}About the weather, or... school assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.39,0:39:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要找到\N{\rEng}Anything to have the chance to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.14,0:39:38.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用眼神交流的机会\N{\rEng}communicate with the language of eye contact.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.93,0:39:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有对计划的信心\N{\rEng}And project confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.70,0:39:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别让头发挡着眼\N{\rEng}And keep the hair out of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.00,0:39:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感受那气氛\N{\rEng}Feel the vibe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.11,0:39:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,做你自己就好了 对\N{\rEng}Just do your stuff. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.25,0:40:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"飓风"是自然界\N{\rEng}The word ''hurricane'' was the name
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.03,0:40:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最强的风暴\N{\rEng}given to Nature's strongest storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.32,0:40:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当高压气团与低压气团相遇时\N{\rEng}A hurricane occurs when high pressure and low pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.07,0:40:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就会形成飓风\N{\rEng}masses of air come into contact with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.76,0:40:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两种气团通常\N{\rEng}There is often a significant difference
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.76,0:40:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,存在显著的气温差异\N{\rEng}in temperature between the two masses.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.87,0:40:24.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一种是暖的 另一种是冷的\N{\rEng}One mass is warm, while the other is cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.14,0:40:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,暖气团上升 冷气团下降\N{\rEng}The warmer air rises and the cooler air falls.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.54,0:40:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,同时 低压气团\N{\rEng}Likewise, the low pressure area
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.59,0:40:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从高压气团的边缘滑下\N{\rEng}slides down the sides of the high pressure area.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.48,0:40:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它们互相绕着彼此打转\N{\rEng}They swirl around one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.99,0:40:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是风暴的开始\N{\rEng}creating the beginnings of the storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.56,0:40:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从这幅\N{\rEng}With this footage
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.53,0:40:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美国海军气象巡逻机拍的图象来看\N{\rEng}taken from US Navy weather patrol aircraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.26,0:40:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以发现\N{\rEng}we can observe two masses,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.25,0:40:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,高低压气团\N{\rEng}one high pressure and one low pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.79,0:40:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彼此接触了\N{\rEng}coming in contact with one and another.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.74,0:41:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结果产生了极具破坏性\N{\rEng}The result is a surging storm of tremendous strength
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.64,0:41:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且强有力的大风暴\N{\rEng}that strikes with forceful determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.65,0:41:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,尽管飓风\N{\rEng}Even though the hurricane
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.93,0:41:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是我们所知的最强风暴\N{\rEng}is the most powerful storm known to us
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.33,0:41:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它袭击大块陆地\N{\rEng}it strikes large land areas
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.75,0:41:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,比如大洲或大的岛屿\N{\rEng}such as continents or large islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.79,0:41:21.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而且消退缓慢\N{\rEng}and slowly dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.83,0:41:25.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是蒙特顾马先生 他最恶心了\N{\rEng}Mr. Montgomery, his ass is grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.14,0:41:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想约你出去\N{\rEng}l want to ask you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.64,0:41:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没门\N{\rEng}Fat chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.15,0:41:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,首先 我要去你家看电视 First, I'll go over to your house and watch the tube.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.39,0:41:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接着我会邀你出去 And then I'm gonna ask you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.50,0:41:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你真是人间尤物\N{\rEng}You're the stone fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.38,0:42:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,飓风\N{\rEng}The hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.42,0:42:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大自然孕育出的\N{\rEng}One of the most awesome and spectacular stories
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.09,0:42:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最壮丽的史诗之一\N{\rEng}Nature has to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.11,0:42:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是几频道? 五\N{\rEng}What channel is this? Five.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.12,0:42:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 来看看…\N{\rEng}Oh. Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.45,0:42:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"野生动物 穿越非洲卡拉哈里沙漠的旅行"\N{\rEng}''Animals in The Wild. Journey through the African Kalahari
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.92,0:42:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"观赏自然栖息地中的动物"\N{\rEng}''and see animals in their natural habitat.''
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.03,0:42:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得听上去不错 你说呢?\N{\rEng}l think that sounds nice, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.93,0:42:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,广大的雨林最终让位给了草原\N{\rEng}This huge rainforest eventually gives way to grasslands
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.34,0:42:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它往四周无限延伸\N{\rEng}that stretch to the horizon in all directions
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.55,0:42:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是卡拉哈里\N{\rEng}this is the Kalahari.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.88,0:42:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想再要点可乐吗? 是的 当然 谢谢\N{\rEng}Do you want some more pop? Yeah, sure. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.19,0:42:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.19,0:43:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,草原上的繁荣景象日渐衰竭\N{\rEng}The wildlife spectacle played out on these grasslands,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.33,0:43:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而休眠中的雨林\N{\rEng}and in recesses of the rainforest
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.93,0:43:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,将在世界各地苏醒\N{\rEng}is unparalleled anywhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.41,0:43:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯 把脚放下去\N{\rEng}Lux, put your feet down, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.05,0:43:29.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卡拉哈里和浩瀚的苍穹\N{\rEng}The Kalahari and its vast open sky
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.22,0:43:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为兽群以及猎食的\N{\rEng}provide a theatre for the life and death drama
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.22,0:43:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大型猫科动物\N{\rEng}played out by the herds
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.13,0:43:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上演的生死循环戏码提供了舞台\N{\rEng}and the great hunting cats that play on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.60,0:43:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 天哪!\N{\rEng}Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.63,0:43:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在已经很晚了 亲爱的? let’s getting so late. Honey...?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.34,0:43:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说已经很晚了\N{\rEng}l said it's getting late.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.65,0:43:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 把电视关了吧\N{\rEng}Oh. Well, let's hit the TV button.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.61,0:43:55.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 呃…\N{\rEng}Right. Err...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.69,0:44:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 谢谢\N{\rEng}OK. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.09,0:44:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴见到你 里斯本太太 是的\N{\rEng}lt was nice to meet you Mrs. Lisbon. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.76,0:44:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚安 再见\N{\rEng}Good night. See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.38,0:44:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\rEng}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.72,0:44:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\rEng}Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.16,0:45:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得回去\N{\rEng}l've got to get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.19,0:46:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是第四节课 你应该第五节课来 不是吗？\N{\rEng}This is fourth period, l don't have you until fifth, do l?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.76,0:46:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道 我不是为数学来的 先生\N{\rEng}l know. I'm not here for math today, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.10,0:46:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我来告诉你\N{\rEng} I'm here to tell you that my intentions for your daughter are entirely honorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.45,0:46:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对你女儿的意图是真心的
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.31,0:46:33.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么意图?\N{\rEng}What might those intentions be?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.47,0:46:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邀勒克斯去校园舞会\N{\rEng}I want to ask Lux to the Homecoming Dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.98,0:46:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,崔普 先坐下吧\N{\rEng}Trip, why don't you sit down for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.99,0:46:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 我妻子和我有明确的规则\N{\rEng}You see, my wife and l have certain rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.26,0:46:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这约束了大女儿\N{\rEng}They were the rules for the older girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.03,0:46:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能为了小女儿开先例\N{\rEng}l can't change them for the younger ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.53,0:46:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算我想 我妻子也不会同意的\N{\rEng}Even if l wanted to, the wife wouldn't let me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.13,0:47:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以 如果你想再来看电视\N{\rEng}So, if you want to come over and watch television again
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.54,0:47:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那可以\N{\rEng}that would be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.52,0:47:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但你不能带勒克斯出去 特别是乘车\N{\rEng}But you cannot take Lux out. Especially not in a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.14,0:47:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以不好意思 年轻人 这是我们的规矩\N{\rEng}So I'm sorry, son, that's just our policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.52,0:47:19.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 先生 如果我们几个男孩\N{\rEng}OK, sir. What if a bunch of us guys
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.89,0:47:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邀请你所有女儿们\N{\rEng}and we took all your daughters out in a group
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.32,0:47:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并在你规定的时间把她们送回去呢?\N{\rEng}and had them back by the time you said?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.59,0:47:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你是橄榄球队的吗? 是的 先生\N{\rEng}Are you on the football squad, son? Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.23,0:47:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么位置? 四分卫\N{\rEng}What position? Defence quarterback.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.30,0:47:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好样的\N{\rEng}Ah, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.40,0:47:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以前… 我当年可是中卫\N{\rEng}l was a... l was a safety in my day.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.94,0:47:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗯 那是个重要位置 先生\N{\rEng}Well, that's a crucial position, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.37,0:47:42.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得分全靠你了 不错!\N{\rEng}Nothing between you and the goal line. Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.81,0:47:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 好吧 是这样的 先生\N{\rEng}Oh, well. So the thing is, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.87,0:47:48.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有场比赛\N{\rEng}We've got the big game
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.85,0:47:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,之后还有舞会\N{\rEng}and then afterwards we've got the dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.89,0:47:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,其他人都有舞伴了\N{\rEng}All the other guys are taking dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.06,0:47:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你很帅 很多女孩愿意跟你出去\N{\rEng}You're good looking. Lots of girls would go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.13,0:48:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对她们不感兴趣 先生\N{\rEng}I'm not interested in lots of girls, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.90,0:48:13.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会跟我妻子商量的 崔普 我尽量\N{\rEng}I'll take it up with the wife, Trip. Do what l can.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.81,0:48:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 先生\N{\rEng}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.61,0:48:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这可是门手艺\N{\rEng}lt's a craft. Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.89,0:48:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,崔普·方汀和几个橄榄球队的男孩\N{\rEng}Trip Fontaine and some of the boys in the football squad
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.00,0:48:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想带她们去校园舞会\N{\rEng}have asked to take the girls to the Homecoming Dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.43,0:48:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道我对那个怎么想\N{\rEng}You know how l feel about that sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.17,0:48:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会保驾护航的 妈妈 拜托!\N{\rEng}I'm a chaperone at the dance. Oh, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.37,0:48:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你爸爸和我等会儿再商量\N{\rEng}Your father and l will discuss it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.61,0:48:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,方汀先生 能跟你说句话吗?\N{\rEng}Mr. Fontaine, may l speak with you, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.32,0:49:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,关于你的请求 我和我妻子已经决定了…\N{\rEng}My wife and l have come to a decision about your request...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.73,0:49:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好极了!\N{\rEng}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.21,0:49:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要带勒克斯·里斯本去校园舞会\N{\rEng}I'm taking Lux Lisbon to Homecoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.74,0:49:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还需要三个人带其他几个女孩\N{\rEng}l need three guys to take the other girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.02,0:49:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我给你三支大麻 崔普\N{\rEng}I'll give you three joints, Trip.\NPick me. We can take my dad's Caddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.48,0:49:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,选我吧 我们可以开我爸的大众
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.99,0:49:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也得叫上我 崔普斯特\N{\rEng}You gotta pick me, Tripster.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.30,0:49:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,崔普 伙计 你欠我的\N{\rEng}Trip, man. You owe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.17,0:49:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我那次从伍德哈斯手里救了你一命\N{\rEng}l saved your ass with Woodhouse that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.90,0:49:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢 爸爸 其他男孩是谁?\N{\rEng}Thanks, Dad. Who are the other boys?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.24,0:49:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们看看 帕克·德顿 杰克·克拉尼\N{\rEng}Let's see. Parker Denton, Jake Conley
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.86,0:49:56.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是个好学生\N{\rEng}he's a good student, dear
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.91,0:49:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有凯文·海德\N{\rEng}and Kevin Head.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.21,0:50:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁带谁? 各凭本事吧\N{\rEng}Who's taking who? They're going to raffle us off.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.25,0:50:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女孩们选择哪件并不要紧\N{\rEng}lt didn't make any difference which dress the girls chose.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.76,0:50:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本太太在胸部加了一寸\N{\rEng}Mrs. Lisbon added an inch to the bust line
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.09,0:50:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,腰部加了两寸\N{\rEng}and two to the waist and hems.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.16,0:50:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,裙子变成了四个一样的麻袋\N{\rEng}The dresses became four identical sacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.93,0:50:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都准备好了? 是的\N{\rEng}Everybody decent? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.87,0:50:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 来吧\N{\rEng}OK. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.41,0:50:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哦 抱歉 好了\N{\rEng}Oh, I'm sorry. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.84,0:50:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 离近点\N{\rEng}Come on. Together.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.34,0:50:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说茄子\N{\rEng}And cheddar cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.98,0:50:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真兴奋!\N{\rEng}Oh, it's so exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.51,0:51:04.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,准备好了吗?  好了 伙计\N{\rEng}Are we ready?  Ready, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.44,0:51:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,行动吧\N{\rEng}Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.65,0:51:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最后帕克因为那辆大众而胜出\N{\rEng}ln the end Parkie won because of the Cadillac,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.85,0:51:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯文·海德因为超猛的大麻\N{\rEng}Kevin Head, because he had the killer weed,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.82,0:51:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有周·黑尔·克拉尼 因为他获奖无数\N{\rEng}and Joe Hill Conley because he won all the school prizes
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.99,0:51:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,崔普认为这些能打动里斯本夫妇\N{\rEng}which Trip thought would impress Mr. and Mrs. Lisbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.76,0:51:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们好 男孩们  你好 里斯本太太\N{\rEng}Hello, boys.  Hello, Mrs. Lisbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.20,0:51:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进来吧  谢谢\N{\rEng}Come in.  Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.05,0:51:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁开车?  是我\N{\rEng}Who's driving?  l am.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.35,0:51:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有驾照多长时间了?\N{\rEng}How long have you had your license?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.10,0:51:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,两个月 但我学了一年\N{\rEng}Two months. l was a learner for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.69,0:51:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们几乎没有乘车出去过\N{\rEng}The girls almost never go out in cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.50,0:51:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最近有很多车祸\N{\rEng}There's so many accidents now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.24,0:52:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们要小心  好的\N{\rEng}I'm sure you'll be very careful.  Oh, yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.50,0:52:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的 最后评估完毕\N{\rEng}OK. The third degree's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.64,0:52:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女孩们!\N{\rEng}Girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.51,0:52:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得走了 舞会见\N{\rEng}I'd better go. See you at the dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.36,0:52:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到时见 里斯本先生\N{\rEng}See you there, Mr. Lisbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.75,0:52:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见 亲爱的\N{\rEng}Bye, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.52,0:52:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女孩们 下来\N{\rEng}Girls. Come on down.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.46,0:52:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,男孩们来了\N{\rEng}The boys are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.98,0:52:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们选的白色 因为不知道你们要穿什么\N{\rEng}We got white ones. We didn't know what you were wearing
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.42,0:53:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,花店的人说白色百搭\N{\rEng}and the flower guy said that white would go with anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.49,0:53:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很高兴你选白色\N{\rEng}I'm glad you got white.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.33,0:53:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不帮她们别上呢?\N{\rEng}Why don't you pin them on?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.63,0:53:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fs18\b1}崔普
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.03,0:53:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了 好了  我们走吧\N{\rEng}There we go.  All right, let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.33,0:53:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了\N{\rEng}Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.93,0:53:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见 妈妈\N{\rEng}Bye, Mum.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.48,0:53:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上帝 看啊! 那辆车又停在那儿了!\N{\rEng}Oh, gosh, look! The car's there again!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.58,0:53:57.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我确定李先生跟她有一腿\N{\rEng}I'm sure Mr. Lea's having an affair with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.03,0:54:00.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我见过他跟着她进了洗衣室\N{\rEng}I saw her followed her into the laundry room.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.82,0:54:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他那个红鼻子真可悲\N{\rEng}He's so sad with that red nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.93,0:54:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能是个酒鬼\N{\rEng}Probably an alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.44,0:54:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,海兹家的人呢？你知道他们是纳粹\N{\rEng}Yep,what about the Hessed?The Hesses are Nazis.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.05,0:54:09.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是纳粹的拥护者\N{\rEng}They're Nazi sympathizers.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.33,0:54:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们在史沃兹小姐\N{\rEng}They had a fit when Miss Schwartz
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.83,0:54:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进网球俱乐部时大发雷霆\N{\rEng}tried to join the tennis club.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.73,0:54:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,铝边侧线不错!他们真觉得这样没问题吗?\N{\rEng}Nice aluminum siding! Do they really think that looks OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.64,0:54:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彼特丝先生从电视上订的\N{\rEng}Mr. Peters ordered that from TV later that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.31,0:54:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是巴蒂诺家的烧烤木桩\N{\rEng}lt's a Baldinos barbecue tree stump.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.78,0:54:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从没见过他们在那上面烧烤!\N{\rEng}l have never seen a barbecue on that thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.75,0:54:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 那是鲨鱼老兵的逃生隧道\N{\rEng}Actually, it's an escape tunnel for the Shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.98,0:54:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,通向河边和他的快艇\N{\rEng}lt leads to the river and his speedboat.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.72,0:54:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗经常去\N{\rEng}Paul goes down there all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.31,0:54:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他可以从下水道去任何一家的地下室\N{\rEng}He can get into anyone's basement through the sewers.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.46,0:54:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不可能! 是的\N{\rEng}No way! Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.57,0:54:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸爸会闻出来的 不会 我有薄荷糖\N{\rEng}Dad'll smell it on you. No, l got mints.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.95,0:55:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会闻到你衣服上的味\N{\rEng}He'll smell it on your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.57,0:55:06.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就说有人在厕所里抽烟\N{\rEng}I'll say they were smoking in the toilets.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.42,0:55:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死前先破个雏吧(烟圈) 真恶心\N{\rEng}Don't let it die a virgin. That's gross.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.42,0:55:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成熟点吧 克拉尼\N{\rEng}Yeah, grow up, Conley.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.88,0:56:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,想跳舞吗? 当然\N{\rEng}Do you want to dance? Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.89,0:56:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跳舞吗?\N{\rEng}Dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.38,0:56:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天气真不错 是吧?\N{\rEng}We've been having such lovely weather, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.05,0:56:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 不错… 很好\N{\rEng}Yeah, we have... Nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.36,0:56:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,晚上好 能请大家注意一下吗?\N{\rEng}Good evening. Could l have your attention for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.09,0:56:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望大家能过的愉快 看起来正是如此\N{\rEng}l hope you're having a good time. lt sure looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.77,0:57:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,舞会委员会可是使出浑身解数\N{\rEng}The dance committee really outdid themselves this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.07,0:57:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,返校节舞王舞后的投票开始\N{\rEng} I'd like to open the voting for Homecoming King and Queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.27,0:57:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投票箱就在那边 请投票\N{\rEng}The ballot box is over there, so please vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.18,0:57:12.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随后我们将宣布结果\N{\rEng}And we'll make the announcement in a little while.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.06,0:57:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢\N{\rEng}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.82,0:57:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有人看到你过来吗? 没有\N{\rEng}Did anybody see you come in? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.35,0:57:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你呢? 没有\N{\rEng}What about you? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.16,0:57:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会喜欢的\N{\rEng}You'll love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.17,0:57:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,蜜桃松子酒\N{\rEng}Peach schnapps.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.97,0:57:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,漂亮女孩都喜欢\N{\rEng}Babes love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.16,0:58:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,味道真好\N{\rEng}That stuff tastes really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.09,0:58:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不想要 谢谢\N{\rEng}l don't want any, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.16,0:58:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托 就尝一下 尝一小口\N{\rEng}Go on, just a taste. A tiny taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.30,0:58:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别当乖乖女了\N{\rEng}Don't be such a goody goody.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.21,0:58:16.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别咽下去\N{\rEng}Don't swallow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.60,0:59:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家请注意\N{\rEng}Can l have everyone's attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.86,0:59:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请大家鼓掌欢迎\N{\rEng} I'd like you to put your hands together
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.60,0:59:17.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今年的舞王舞后…\N{\rEng}for this year's Kind and Queen...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.20,0:59:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,崔普·方汀和勒克斯·里斯本\N{\rEng}Trip Fontaine and Lux Lisbon.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.96,1:00:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是我最快乐的时光!\N{\rEng} I'm having the best time!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.45,1:01:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们出去走走吧\N{\rEng}Let's go for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.78,1:01:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是算了 我一会儿得回来\N{\rEng} I'd better not. l've got to go back in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.19,1:01:14.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以盯着车\N{\rEng}We can keep an eye on the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.88,1:01:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不会不等我们就走的\N{\rEng}They won't leave without us.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.42,1:01:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我爸爸…\N{\rEng}My dad...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.93,1:01:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,告诉他你要把皇冠放到柜子里\N{\rEng}Tell him you're putting the crown in your locker.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.37,1:01:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到那块草皮了吗? 嗯?\N{\rEng}See that divot there? Uh huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.80,1:01:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我今天就在那儿放倒了那小子\N{\rEng}That's where l reamed this guy today.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.27,1:01:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,全防住了  真的吗?\N{\rEng}A cross body block.  Really?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.98,1:01:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可能他们跟你爸爸回去了吧?  未必\N{\rEng}Maybe they went home with your dad?  l doubt it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.62,1:01:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们完了 是勒克斯 不是我们\N{\rEng}We're cooked. Luxy is, we're not.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.74,1:02:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁有薄荷糖?\N{\rEng}Does anyone have any mints?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.37,1:02:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉 没有\N{\rEng}Sorry. No.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.15,1:02:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见 帕克\N{\rEng}Bye, Parkie.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.25,1:02:20.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们送你们到门口  不 不必了\N{\rEng}We'll walk you to the door.  No, don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.52,1:02:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为什么不行?  真的不必了\N{\rEng}Why not?  Just don't.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.43,1:02:28.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好的\N{\rEng}OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.00,1:02:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你会给我打电话吗?\N{\rEng}Will you call me?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.20,1:02:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然!\N{\rEng}Absolutely!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.77,1:02:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见\N{\rEng}Bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.37,1:02:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再见 再见\N{\rEng}Bye. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.10,1:05:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你还好吗? 你去哪儿了?\N{\rEng}Are you OK? Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.14,1:05:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看你这个样子! 进屋去!\N{\rEng}Look at the state of you! Get in the house!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.39,1:05:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那晚我独自走回家了\N{\rEng}l walked home alone that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.91,1:05:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不关心她怎么回去 很奇怪\N{\rEng}l didn't care how she got home. lt was weird.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.06,1:05:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是说 我喜欢她 我非常喜欢她\N{\rEng}l mean, l liked her. l liked her a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.80,1:05:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但那晚在操场…\N{\rEng}But out there on the field...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.60,1:05:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就是另一回事了\N{\rEng}lt was just different then.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.60,1:06:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是我最后一次见她\N{\rEng}That was the last time l saw her.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.98,1:06:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道 大多数人从没尝过那种爱情\N{\rEng}You know, most people will never taste that kind of love.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.18,1:06:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但至少我经历过一次 对吗?\N{\rEng}But at least l tasted it once, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.02,1:06:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,您应该去开六点钟的群会了\N{\rEng}lt's time for your six o'clock group meeting.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.91,1:06:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对勒克斯的晚归\N{\rEng}Given Lux's failure to make curfew
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.07,1:06:39.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,大家都预料到了坏结果\N{\rEng}everyone expected a crackdown.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.45,1:06:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但没人想到会如此惨烈\N{\rEng}But few anticipated it would be so drastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.82,1:06:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女孩们被禁止上学\N{\rEng}The girls were taken out of school
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.50,1:06:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本太太\N{\rEng}and Mrs. Lisbon shut the house
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.24,1:06:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以最大的安全措施封锁了她家\N{\rEng}in maximum security isolation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.52,1:06:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她不止不让女孩们上学\N{\rEng}She did more than taking the girls out of school.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.69,1:06:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个星期天 在一场教堂说教后\N{\rEng}That Sunday, after a spirited church sermon.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.93,1:07:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本太太让勒克斯销毁她的唱片\N{\rEng}Mrs. Lisbon made Lux destroy her records.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.47,1:07:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快点!\N{\rEng}Now!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.07,1:07:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是 妈妈…\N{\rEng}But, Mum...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.14,1:07:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我最后再说一遍 勒克斯\N{\rEng}This is final, Luxy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.81,1:07:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这不公平  我说快点\N{\rEng}That's not fair.  l said now.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.49,1:07:30.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就现在 勒克斯!\N{\rEng}Now, Luxy!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.98,1:07:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快点儿\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.32,1:07:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,热吻乐队 请别让我这么做\N{\rEng}Kiss. Please don't make me do this.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.12,1:07:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,烧了它\N{\rEng}Burn it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.40,1:08:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈妈 空中铁匠!\N{\rEng}Oh, Mum, Aerosmith!
