Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.18,1:18:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,该死 是她们\N{\rEng}Shit. lt's them.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.99,1:18:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,回首昨日\N{\rEng}To think that only yesterday
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.99,1:18:39.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我曾无忧无虑\N{\rEng}I was cheerful, bright and gay
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.49,1:18:41.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对无人知晓的未来\N{\rEng}Looking forward to who wouldn't do
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.18,1:18:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,和一切充满希翼\N{\rEng}The role I was about to play?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.99,1:18:47.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,危难之际\N{\rEng}In my hour of need
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.99,1:18:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是真的 再次孤身一人 本就如此\N{\rEng}I truly am indeed Alone again naturally
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.99,1:19:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投入我怀抱 当你孤单的时候\N{\rEng}Run to me whenever you're lonely
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.19,1:19:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,投入我怀抱 每当你需要依靠\N{\rEng}Run to me if you need a shoulder
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.99,1:19:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,某些时刻 你的他应该成熟而可靠\N{\rEng}Now and then, you need someone older
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.99,1:19:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那么 宝贝 来到我的怀抱\N{\rEng}so darling, you run to me
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.99,1:19:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,遥远的彼岸\N{\rEng}So far away
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.99,1:19:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是否仍有人原地驻足\N{\rEng}Doesn't anybody stay in one place anymore
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.99,1:19:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看到你出现在门前 很幸福\N{\rEng}It would be so fine to see your face at my door
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.99,1:19:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,却无从得知 你将时光虚度\N{\rEng}Doesn't help to know You're just time away
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.93,1:19:46.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要回家了 明天见  回见\N{\rEng} I'm going home. See you tomorrow.  See you later.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:50.64,1:19:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们快窒息了 勒克斯  你在这儿很安全\N{\rEng}We're suffocating.  Lux, you're safe here.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.54,1:19:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没法呼吸\N{\rEng}l can't breathe.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.11,1:20:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人接\N{\rEng}No answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.11,1:20:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明天午夜 等我们的信号
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.63,1:20:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几点了?  到时候了\N{\rEng}What time is it?  Any time now.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.60,1:20:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,伙计们 就在那儿  是吗?\N{\rEng}Guys, there it is.  What?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.84,1:20:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 是她们\N{\rEng}Yeah, it's them.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.25,1:20:37.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们走\N{\rEng}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.29,1:20:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有我妈的车钥匙\N{\rEng}l've got the keys to my mum's car.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.02,1:21:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许我们该敲敲门\N{\rEng}Maybe we should knock.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.56,1:21:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们到了\N{\rEng}We're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.64,1:21:39.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到点了 我们在等你们呢\N{\rEng}lt's about time. We've been waiting for you guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.44,1:21:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们有车 装满了油 想去哪儿都行\N{\rEng}We've got a car. We'll take you anywhere you want to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:43.08,1:21:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是辆美洲豹 车厢很大\N{\rEng}lt's a Cougar. lt's got a big trunk.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.35,1:21:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能坐前排吗? 当然\N{\rEng}Can l sit up front? Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.19,1:21:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁挨着我坐?\N{\rEng}Which one of you is going to sit next to me?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.73,1:22:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你父母在哪儿?  睡觉\N{\rEng}Where are your parents?  Asleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.93,1:22:05.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你姐妹们呢? 马上就来\N{\rEng}What about your sisters? They're coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.17,1:22:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,快点 很晚了\N{\rEng}Come on. lt's getting late.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.01,1:22:11.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,再等5分钟\N{\rEng}Wait five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.25,1:22:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得等我父母都睡着\N{\rEng}We have to wait until my parents are asleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.35,1:22:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,得再等会儿 我妈失眠\N{\rEng}They take forever. My mum's an insomniac.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.85,1:22:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最好开我们的车 空间大些\N{\rEng}We'd better take our car, there's more room.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.66,1:22:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你开得了旅行车吗?\N{\rEng}Think you can handle a station wagon?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.92,1:22:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然 又不是手动档 是吧?\N{\rEng}Sure. lt's not a stick, is it?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.66,1:22:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是的 没问题\N{\rEng}No. Yeah, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.40,1:22:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能驾驶吗?  当然\N{\rEng}Will you let me steer?  Sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.04,1:22:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们得走了 我听到有动静 可以是你妈妈\N{\rEng}We should go. l just heard something. lt could be your mum.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.41,1:22:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,进来吧\N{\rEng}Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.29,1:22:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我去车里等\N{\rEng} I'll go wait in the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.44,1:22:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们在这儿等她们吧\N{\rEng}You guys wait here for my sisters.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.55,1:23:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要摸到一个 就能让我疯狂!\N{\rEng}These girls make me crazy. lf l just felt one of them once!
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.22,1:24:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么了?\N{\rEng}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.21,1:24:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们永远无法弄清发生的顺序\N{\rEng}We would never be sure about the sequence of events.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.04,1:24:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到现在我们还在讨论\N{\rEng}We argue about it still.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.32,1:24:32.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很可能 邦妮死时\N{\rEng}Most likely, Bonnie had died
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.92,1:24:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们正在客厅里\N{\rEng}while we were waiting in the living room
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.62,1:24:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,幻想着高速公路\N{\rEng}dreaming of highways.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.36,1:24:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随后玛丽把头伸进了烤箱里\N{\rEng}Mary put her head in the oven shortly thereafter.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.33,1:24:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特瑞丝吃了很多安眠药\N{\rEng}Therese, stuffed with sleeping pills,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:44.80,1:24:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在我们到之前就走了\N{\rEng}was gone by the time we got there.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:48.27,1:24:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,勒克斯是最后一个\N{\rEng}Lux was the last to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.41,1:25:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在是周日下午四点钟\N{\rEng}lt's four o'clock on Sunday afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:01.73,1:25:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道你的孩子在哪儿吗?\N{\rEng}Do you know where your children are?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.78,1:25:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,邦妮 是里斯本姐妹中最小的一个…\N{\rEng}Bonnie, the younger Lisbon sister...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.62,1:25:12.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特瑞丝·里斯本 她很爱马 曾经写信…\N{\rEng}Therese Lisbon, a horse lover, has written to...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:12.49,1:25:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,玛丽想当啦啦队长\N{\rEng}Mary wanted to be a cheerleader,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.34,1:25:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但她妈妈不同意\N{\rEng}but her mother wouldn't let her.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.79,1:25:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在她们的家中自杀…\N{\rEng}..suicide in their house...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.33,1:25:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我愤怒到无以复加\N{\rEng}l wasn't able to express the anger l felt.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.89,1:25:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...莉迪亚·皮尔 八频道新闻\N{\rEng}...Lydia Perl, Channel Eight News.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.41,1:25:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的女儿们并不缺少爱\N{\rEng}None of my daughters lacked for any love.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.55,1:25:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们家里有足够的爱\N{\rEng}There was plenty of love in our house.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.99,1:25:44.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我就是弄不懂为什么\N{\rEng}l never understood why.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.29,1:26:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自杀事件后\N{\rEng}After the suicides,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.59,1:26:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本夫妇放弃了\N{\rEng}Mr and Mrs Lisbon gave up
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.85,1:26:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过正常生活的愿望\N{\rEng}any attempt to lead a normal life.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.23,1:26:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们让海德力先生收拾了房子\N{\rEng}They had Mr. Hadley pack up the house,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.13,1:26:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把能卖的家具都贱卖了\N{\rEng}and sell the furniture in a garage sale.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.70,1:26:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,里斯本先生把房子卖给一对波士顿年轻夫妇\N{\rEng}Mr. Lisbon sold the house to a young couple from Boston.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.18,1:26:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当然\N{\rEng}We, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.06,1:26:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们从垃圾堆里拣来了家庭相册\N{\rEng}took the family photos that were put out with the trash.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.85,1:26:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最终 我们拼凑出了谜团的答案\N{\rEng}ln the end, we had pieces of the puzzle,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.87,1:26:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但裂痕仍在\N{\rEng}but how to put them together,gaps still remained.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.82,1:26:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,形状奇怪的空白\N{\rEng}Oddly shaped emptiness,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.02,1:26:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在环绕之物的映射下\N{\rEng}mapped by what surrounded them,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.13,1:26:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就像叫不出名字的国度\N{\rEng}like countries we couldn't name.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.97,1:27:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,徘徊在她们身后的并非生命\N{\rEng}What lingered after them was not life,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.57,1:27:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而是现实生活中最琐碎的物件\N{\rEng}but the most trivial list of mundane facts
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.14,1:27:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,墙上滴答作响的钟摆\N{\rEng}a clock ticking on the wall,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.95,1:27:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正午昏暗的房间\N{\rEng}a room dim at noon,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.55,1:27:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,人类自私的暴行\N{\rEng}the outrageousness of a human being
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.93,1:27:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,自行其道\N{\rEng}thinking only of herself
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.82,1:27:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们开始徒劳的试图忘记她们\N{\rEng}We began the impossible process of trying to forget them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.30,1:27:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的父母做能的更好\N{\rEng}Our parents were able to do this,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:40.74,1:27:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们回到网球组和鸡尾酒会上\N{\rEng}returning to their tennis foursomes and cocktails
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.80,1:27:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,处变不惊\N{\rEng}as though they'd seen it all before.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.25,1:27:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盛夏又到来了\N{\rEng}lt was full fledged summer again
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.91,1:27:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在塞西利亚割腕一年后\N{\rEng}over a year after Cecilia had slit her wrists
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.62,1:27:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,空气中充满了毒药\N{\rEng}spreading the poison in the air.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.19,1:27:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,疯长的植物增加了湖里的磷肥\N{\rEng}A spill at the plant increased the lake's phosphates
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.05,1:28:00.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并产生大量藻类\N{\rEng}and produced algae
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.46,1:28:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,沼泽的气味\N{\rEng}so that the swamp's smell
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.09,1:28:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,环绕着这座气派的公馆\N{\rEng}filled the air infiltrating the genteel mansions.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.00,1:28:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,少女们初登社会\N{\rEng}Debutantes cried at coming out in a season
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.15,1:28:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个人却只记得那时的恶臭\N{\rEng}remembered for its bad smell.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.94,1:28:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,而奥康纳家人的别出心裁\N{\rEng}The O'Connors ingeniously made
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.97,1:28:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,给女儿爱丽丝的\N{\rEng}the theme of their daughter
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.23,1:28:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,成人派对命名为"窒息"\N{\rEng}Alice's debutante party ''Asphyxiation''.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.13,1:28:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,像大家一样\N{\rEng}Like everyone else,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.30,1:28:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们渐渐忘了里斯本家的女孩\N{\rEng}we went to forget about the Lisbon girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.79,1:28:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她会让他心脏病发的\N{\rEng}She'll give him a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.90,1:29:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,嗨 帕克\N{\rEng}Hi, Parkie.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.21,1:29:25.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,会装死的虫子如何?\N{\rEng}How about the acting bug?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.34,1:29:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从檎基抓来的\N{\rEng}l caught it from Kinky.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.98,1:29:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我今晚想宣布\N{\rEng}And l want to announce tonight that
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.80,1:29:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下个秋天 爱丽丝就要去纽瀚文上学了\N{\rEng}next fall Alice is going to school in Newhaven.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.16,1:29:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听说那里的语法学校十分了得\N{\rEng}l hear they have a great grammar school up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.79,1:29:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 就是萨姆的爸爸建的 是吧?\N{\rEng}ln fact, Sam's father built it, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.76,1:29:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是医院 保罗\N{\rEng}The hospital, Paul.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.70,1:29:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们十分为爱丽丝自豪 万分自豪\N{\rEng}We're so proud of Alice. We couldn't be prouder.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.44,1:29:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这杯敬她\N{\rEng}Here's to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.61,1:30:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我受够了 再见 残酷世界\N{\rEng}l've had it. Goodbye cruel world.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.22,1:30:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不 不 不! 你不会理解我的\N{\rEng}No, no, no! You don't understand me.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.23,1:30:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是少年 我有烦恼\N{\rEng} I'm a teenager, l got problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.87,1:30:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些年来 有许多关于她们的流言蜚语\N{\rEng}So much has been said about the girls over the years,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.88,1:30:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我们从未找到过答案\N{\rEng}but we have never found an answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:37.05,1:30:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这与她们的早逝无关\N{\rEng}lt didn't matter how old they had been,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.89,1:30:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抑或因为她们是女孩\N{\rEng}or that they were girls,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.26,1:30:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只因为我们爱过她们\N{\rEng}but only that we had loved them.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.97,1:30:51.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们始终听不见\N{\rEng}And that they hadn't heard us call them,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.63,1:30:56.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在门外的呐喊\N{\rEng}still do not hear us calling them out of those rooms
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.03,1:30:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们始终在那里孤独着\N{\rEng}where they went to be alone for all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.44,1:31:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们永远无法将它们拼贴完整\N{\rEng}We will never find the pieces to put them back together.

